#!/bin/bash
# PostToolUse telemetry (matcher: Bash|mcp__codebase-memory-mcp__.*).
# Appends one timestamped line per CBM tool invocation to
# .devforge/cbm-usage.log so adoption can be measured later. Always exit 0;
# never blocks (PostToolUse exit 2 is ignored anyway).
TOOL=$(python3 -c "import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('tool_name',''))" 2>/dev/null)
[ -z "$TOOL" ] && exit 0
LOG="${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR:-.}/.devforge/cbm-usage.log"
mkdir -p "$(dirname "$LOG")" 2>/dev/null
echo "$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) $TOOL" >> "$LOG" 2>/dev/null
exit 0
